# Web Application Projects - AI Development Rules

## Project Context
This folder contains 25 full-stack web applications with AI integration using modern frameworks (React, Next.js, Vue, Angular, Node.js).

## Technology Stack
- **Frontend**: React.js, Next.js, Vue.js, Angular, HTML5, CSS3, TypeScript
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js, Python (Django, FastAPI)
- **APIs**: RESTful APIs, GraphQL
- **AI/ML**: TensorFlow.js, OpenAI APIs, HuggingFace, Google Cloud AI, AWS AI Services
- **Database**: MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Redis, Firebase, Vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate)

## Development Guidelines

### Code Standards
- Use TypeScript for type safety in all new code
- Follow component-based architecture patterns
- Implement proper error handling and validation
- Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations

### AI Integration Best Practices
- Implement proper API rate limiting and error handling for AI services
- Cache AI responses where appropriate to reduce costs
- Use environment variables for API keys (never commit secrets)
- Implement fallback mechanisms when AI services are unavailable
- Monitor AI API usage and costs

### Project Structure
```
project-name/
├── src/
│   ├── components/     # Reusable UI components
│   ├── pages/          # Page components
│   ├── services/       # API and AI service integrations
│   ├── utils/          # Helper functions
│   ├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks
│   └── types/          # TypeScript type definitions
├── public/             # Static assets
├── tests/              # Test files
└── package.json
```

### Testing Requirements
- Write unit tests for utility functions and services
- Implement integration tests for API endpoints
- Test AI integration with mock responses
- Ensure responsive design across devices

### Security Considerations
- Validate all user inputs
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Use HTTPS for all API communications
- Sanitize data before AI processing
- Follow OWASP security guidelines

### Performance Optimization
- Implement lazy loading for components
- Optimize images and assets
- Use code splitting
- Implement caching strategies
- Monitor and optimize AI API response times

### Deployment
- Use Docker for containerization
- Implement CI/CD pipelines
- Use environment-specific configurations
- Monitor application performance and errors

## Common AI Features
- Product recommendations and content filtering
- Natural language processing and chatbots
- Sentiment analysis and text classification
- Image recognition and processing
- Predictive analytics and forecasting

## Getting Started
```bash
cd <project-folder>
npm install
npm run dev
```

